message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Succession: Guided Behavioral Evolution for LLM Agents"
abstract: "A three-generation framework for behavioral continuity in LLM coding agents. Succession detects user corrections organically, extracts them into persistent rule files with three enforcement tiers (mechanical, semantic, advisory), and enforces them across sessions — immune to instruction drift. On SuccessionBench, instruction drift is measurable at 150k tokens, corrections degrade at depth, and periodic re-injection is the most effective mitigation."
